                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/7–754: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Philippines</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">limited official use</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-12T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 12, 1954—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>134. Secretary emphasized our position re Communist China to
                        <persName>Garcia</persName> but did not elicit direct response. Suggest you
                    reiterate our strong opposition to seating Communist China to
                        <persName>Neri</persName> or Foreign Office using as basis statement by
                    President and Secretary contained daily wireless file 150 and 151 July 7 and
                    8.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
